## Introduction to Events

### Vocabulary

- **Event-driven program**:  A program designed to run blocks of code or functions in response to specified events (e.g. a mouse click)
- **Event:** A user action or other occurrence that can be detected by a program. Events can be used to trigger execution of specific blocks of code
- **Event Handler:** Indicates which commands should run when a specified event occurs
- **Element ID:** A unique ID given to a UI element (such as a button) so that an event handler can be attached to that specific element only

