## User Interface and Apps

### Vocabulary

- **Design Mode:** Specific to the App Lab programming environment, "Design Mode" refers to the area of the environment where students can simply drag and drag UI elements into their app, and set certain properties like color, size, text, etc. With Design Mode, the process of app development in App Lab changes slightly, as prior to the introduction of design mode, students could only use functions in code such as  `button()` to create a button on the screen:
  - First, students will drag and drop UI elements in Design Mode to create the visual layout of their app.
  - As they are creating the layout, they should give design elements (such as buttons) unique and descriptive **IDs**.
  -  Students then return to "Code Mode" for their app to program event handlers for many of those UI elements to respond to user input.

<img src="https://images.code.org/0de10d7ed39725856a38f07cad4de79b-image-1446419972230.gif" style="width:500px;margin-left:100px;">

- **Code Mode:** Up until the introduction of Design Mode, all students have experienced of App Lab is what we refer to as "Code Mode." Code Mode is where students write the brains and actual functionality of the app, as adding UI elements in Design Mode simply places them on the screen. Those elements will not be interactive until they are programmed by the student.

<img src="https://images.code.org/c81d8889ebfdc47c461ce9e9cc537e24-image-1446420240257.gif" style="width:500px;margin-left:100px;">

